is getting married at 18.

13:37.859 --> 13:40.568
I forbid it. Forbidden!

13:51.498 --> 13:53.480
Peter, I'm sorry,
I'm just not okay

13:53.542 --> 13:56.835
with our daughter marrying
someone who is clearly gay.

13:57.028 --> 13:58.561
You know,
you're starting to sound

13:58.621 --> 14:00.487
an awful lot
like your own mother.

14:00.507 --> 14:01.989
This isn't gonna be good
for either of them.

14:02.050 --> 14:03.766
Lois, let me ask you something.

14:03.793 --> 14:06.511
What's the best-case scenario
for someone like Meg?

14:06.704 --> 14:10.089
Dying alone in a lighthouse?
Maybe Bruce changed.

14:10.183 --> 14:12.075
And-and either way,
Meg's happy for once.

14:12.093 --> 14:13.476
I say we go with it.

14:14.971 --> 14:16.688
It's gonna be all right.

14:16.839 --> 14:17.930
No, it's not gonna be all right.

14:18.024 --> 14:19.173
It's never gonna
be all right again

14:19.234 --> 14:20.433
if they go through with this.

14:20.585 --> 14:22.176
Peter, we got to do...

14:22.195 --> 14:24.103
Get a hold of yourself, woman.
She's coming downstairs.

14:24.197 --> 14:26.589
Well, there's the bride-to-be.

14:26.649 --> 14:28.608
-Oh, hey, Mom.
-Listen, Meg,

14:28.760 --> 14:30.943
I was hoping we could
put all this behind us.

14:31.037 --> 14:32.762
I'd like that.

14:32.780 --> 14:35.615
That's better. And I'm sorry
for what I said about Bruce.

14:35.709 --> 14:39.285
If you love him, then your
father and I fully support it.

14:39.379 --> 14:41.528
Thanks, Mom.
Speaking of which,

14:41.548 --> 14:43.623
I'm finally gonna meet
Bruce's parents.

14:43.758 --> 14:45.775
Would you guys want to
come to dinner with us?

14:45.793 --> 14:48.294
-Oh, we'd love to come.
-Oh, thank you, Mom.

14:48.388 --> 14:50.889
Family hug. Bring it in.

14:51.057 --> 14:53.057
Seriously, you got
to bring it in.

14:54.919 --> 14:58.379
Oh, Meg, I haven't seen you
smile like this in a long time.

14:58.440 --> 15:00.732
Probably not since you were in
that music video.

