15:12.862 --> 15:14.654
Hey, hey, everybody.

15:14.806 --> 15:17.749
I'd like you to meet my parents
Phil and Candy Straight.

15:17.900 --> 15:20.251
Peter Griffin. My arms
were torn off at a concert.

15:20.420 --> 15:24.422
So, these two lovebirds
are gonna tie the knot.

15:24.591 --> 15:28.334
Yes, a heterosexual marriage,
just like you always wanted.

15:28.428 --> 15:31.154
And I did, too.
All of us did.

15:31.255 --> 15:33.005
Well, as someone
who doesn't get subtext,

15:33.099 --> 15:35.249
I just want to say cheers.

15:35.310 --> 15:37.584
You know what?
This calls for champagne.

15:37.646 --> 15:39.437
-Sir? Excuse me, sir?
-(snapping softly)

15:39.630 --> 15:41.681
Ugh, this waiter is terrible.

15:41.816 --> 15:43.090
Finally.

15:43.109 --> 15:44.684
We would like
your finest champagne

15:44.778 --> 15:47.403
and your longest fork
and knife, please.

15:48.731 --> 15:50.597
So, Phil,
what line of work you in?

15:50.617 --> 15:53.159
Ooh, what did you order? Mind?

15:54.979 --> 15:57.680
(church bell rings)

15:57.740 --> 16:00.850
I can't believe my little girl's
getting married.

16:00.910 --> 16:02.201
You look beautiful, Meg.

16:02.295 --> 16:04.203
Really? You think so?

16:04.297 --> 16:08.040
Uh... uh-huh. Y-Yes.

16:08.134 --> 16:10.343
Five minutes, honey.

16:12.030 --> 16:14.455
The Shropnicks made it
all the way in from Colorado.

16:14.599 --> 16:15.789
How about that?

16:15.850 --> 16:18.059
("Canon in D" playing)

16:22.506 --> 16:24.707
Say hi to the Shropnicks.
They came a long way.

16:24.767 --> 16:28.152
Hi, guys. Thank you so much
for coming all this way.

16:28.321 --> 16:31.030
From Colorado. Where we live.

16:32.608 --> 16:35.493
Dearly beloved,
we are gathered here today

16:35.644 --> 16:40.147
to celebrate the union
of these two very special people

16:40.208 --> 16:42.558
on their very special day.

16:42.618 --> 16:44.818
(quietly) That's Jeffrey,
Bruce's longtime boyfriend.

16:44.838 --> 16:47.672
The priest's voice faded out
and now it'll fade back in

16:47.823 --> 16:49.656
to show that he's further along
in the ceremony.

16:49.759 --> 16:52.159
PRIEST:
...and finally, Edward Zylock.

16:52.220 --> 16:54.420
Fallen heroes, all.

16:54.514 --> 16:56.014
Now, does anyone have any reason

16:56.165 --> 16:58.266
why these two
should not be married?

17:03.047 --> 17:05.189
♪ ♪

17:15.035 --> 17:16.609
I do.

17:16.761 --> 17:18.202
-(all gasping)
-What?
-The bride?

17:18.395 --> 17:20.154
Did you park on the street?
I parked on the street.

17:20.206 --> 17:22.040
I'm sorry, I can't do this.

17:22.233 --> 17:24.116
I know you don't really want
to marry me.

17:24.252 --> 17:27.270
You're only doing this
to make your parents happy.

17:27.330 --> 17:30.106
And I know...

17:30.166 --> 17:34.277
Well, I-I think
I know everything.

17:34.337 --> 17:36.578
What gave it away?

17:36.598 --> 17:38.464
When I saw you
with your parents.

17:38.558 --> 17:40.800
You obviously just want them
off your back.

17:40.952 --> 17:42.451
