17:42.553 --> 17:44.896
is mostly guys' things
next to Comcast remotes.

17:45.089 --> 17:48.624
I only meet the ones
that go past the volume button.

17:48.684 --> 17:51.444
Someone want to tell me
what the hell is going on here?

17:54.991 --> 17:58.392
Mom, Dad, I'm gay.

17:58.453 --> 18:00.136
PETER:
(gasps) What?

18:00.196 --> 18:01.821
LOIS:
Peter, you knew that.

18:01.973 --> 18:03.230
Is this some kind of joke?

18:03.249 --> 18:06.659
This ain't no joke, Daddy.
I like mens.

18:06.753 --> 18:08.753
This feels like an episode
that someone

18:08.946 --> 18:10.980
would get a prize for in 1994.

18:11.040 --> 18:14.333
Maybe we should talk
about this another time, dear.

18:14.485 --> 18:16.410
No. I want to talk
about it now.

18:16.471 --> 18:19.989
I'm gay, and like all gay men,
it was a choice I made

18:20.091 --> 18:23.417
when I couldn't find a table
at the high school cafeteria.

18:23.478 --> 18:26.679
Cork up those ink pots.
We know that's not how it works.

18:26.831 --> 18:28.422
Everyone, thank you for coming,

18:28.483 --> 18:31.925
but I'm afraid there isn't
going to be a wedding today.

18:31.986 --> 18:33.519
Oh, yes, there is.

18:33.655 --> 18:36.739
Jeffrey, get your pimply
little ass up here.

18:38.343 --> 18:40.934
Jeffrey, will you marry me?

18:40.995 --> 18:43.621
Oh, yes.

18:46.126 --> 18:48.442
Come on, Shropnicks,
we're leaving.

18:48.503 --> 18:52.463
Let's start
the 21-hour drive home.

18:52.656 --> 18:55.633
You-you guys can't
get married in the church.

18:55.784 --> 18:59.786
We don't recognize you
as... well, as people.

18:59.889 --> 19:01.455
Ugh, fine.

19:01.558 --> 19:04.200
Everyone, meet us
in the Walgreens parking lot

19:04.260 --> 19:06.644
down the street.

19:06.837 --> 19:09.647
Meg, sweetie, are you okay?

19:09.840 --> 19:12.375
You know what, Mom? I am.

19:12.435 --> 19:14.393
Bruce and Jeffrey
love each other.

19:14.487 --> 19:16.395
They deserve to be happy.

19:16.489 --> 19:18.381
-And so do I.
-Oh, Meg.

19:18.441 --> 19:20.399
Don't make this day about you.

19:20.493 --> 19:23.552
-Oh, Bruce.
-Oh, Jeffrey.

19:23.654 --> 19:25.221
Oh...

19:25.323 --> 19:26.831
No, no, no, no.

19:27.024 --> 19:28.649
No, no, no, no, no.

19:28.710 --> 19:30.209
No.

19:34.698 --> 19:36.340
It's nice
that they're doing this,

19:36.533 --> 19:38.067
but who's gonna marry them?

19:38.127 --> 19:40.494
By the power vested in me,

19:40.513 --> 19:43.181
I pronounce you
husband and husband.

19:43.374 --> 19:45.257
You may kiss when you get home.

19:45.351 --> 19:46.726
Well, we just lost the prize.

